President Biden has declared a state of emergency in Connecticut due to severe storms, flooding, and the potential breach of a dam. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas, including New London County and the Mohegan Tribal Nation and Mashantucket Pequot Tribal Nation. FEMA is authorized to mobilize equipment and resources to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. The federal funding for emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent. Robert V. Fogel of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.